item.title: ONE-ON-ONE BIKE TRAINING // City of Darebin Bike Skills Workshops
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
Course are held throughout the year.

The exact date, time and location is negotiated between you and your instructor.

Time to stop making excuses and start riding!

Our experienced, patient and friendly instructors will start with the absolute basics like how to walk your bike, get on and off gracefully, start off, pedal and stop safely. They’ll give you hands-on support you until you find your balance and then cheer as you cycle off into the sunset! You need a bike (ideally your own, but you can also borrow from a friend or family member or hire a bike), a helmet and some determination. Our training is always tailored to your needs and we are also able to work with clients with special physical requirements or disability. For anyone aged from 7 to 77!  

Two types of bike training are offered:

1. Learn to Ride (3 hrs) - designed for absolute beginners

OR

2. Improve Your Skills (2 hrs) - designed for those with some previous riding experience

 

1. Learn to ride (adults & children)

Our tried and tested training program should get you up and riding within 3 hours!

In these private lessons, you will learn and practice basic but essential bike control skills, such as starting, stopping, using gears, signalling, and scanning in a traffic-free environment. You will also learn strategies for riding safely on paths and local streets.
  • Format for 7-8 year olds: 3 x 1 hour sessions are preferable for younger children
  • Format for those aged 9 and over:  2 x 1.5 hour sessions, usually arranged to be held one week apart.
  This training usually costs $200.  However, Darebin residents are eligible to participate in this training program for the specially discounted price of $100, due to generous subsidies offered by the City of Darebin.  Your session can be scheduled on weekdays/weekends, depending on instructor availability.  Following your registration you will be asked to contact Alicia from Bikes@Work to indicate your date/time/location preferences.  Please note we usually require 10 days notice to set the training up.  Email: alicia@bikesatwork.com.au  tel: 0409 142 264.   

2. Improve your skills (adults & children)

If you know how to ride but are a bit wobbly and lacking in confidence, then this 2 hour private lesson is perfect for you. We’ll practice basic bike control skills including smooth stopping, starting, using gears, scanning, hand signals and emergency stops.
  • Format: 1 x 2 hour session.
This training usually costs $140.  However, Darebin residents are eligible to participate in this training program for the specially discounted price of $70, due to generous subsidies offered by the City of Darebin.  Your session can be scheduled on weekdays/weekends, depending on instructor availability.  Following your registration you will be asked to contact Alicia from Bikes@Work to indicate your date/time/location preferences.  Please note we usually require 10 days notice to set the training up.  Please contact Alicia to arrange the dates, times and a location for this one-on-one training program. Email:alicia@bikesatwork.com.au or 0409 142 264   ADDITIONAL SUPPORT THAT MAY BE AVAILABLE TO YOU: 
Members of the community who are recipients of Centrelink payments or in social housing may be eligible to participate in this training program at no cost.  Please contact Alicia from Bikes@Work to find out more.  Email: alicia@bikesatwork.com.au or  tel:  0409 142 264.  And if you are experiencing financial hardship and do not currently own your own bike, please contact our good friends at WeCycle at wecyclemelbourne@gmail.com. They recycle unwanted bikes and re-home them with people who need them - they may be able to assist you too!  
  FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS Who organises and delivers this training?  
  • This practical one-on-one training program is run by the professionals at Bikes@Work and is proudly supported by the City of Darebin for people who live in the municipality.
Is there an age limit?
  • Yes. One-on-one training course is only available to those aged 7+.  Children under the age of 16 MUST be accompanied by an adult.
What should I bring?
  • A bicycle in good condition with working brakes, a bell and pumped up tyres.
  • A well fitting bicycle helmet.
  • Runners or similar closed-toe footwear.
  • Sun/weather protection.
  • A bottle of water.
  • A snack (optional).
I don't live in Darebin. Can I do this training course?
  • Unfortunately, one-on-one training is only available to Darebin residents.
Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?
  • No. You don't need to bring your ticket on the day.
What is the refund policy?
  • We offer refunds up to 7 days before the workshop.  Unfortunately, we are unable to provide refunds after this time.  However, If you are unable to attend the workshop due to unforeseen circumstances, you may transfer your ticket to another friend or family member by updating your registration online.  If you require assistance with this process, please call us during business hours on 8470-8683 or send an email to: green.travel@darebin.vic.gov..au
The City of Darebin uses Eventbrite for all Bike Skills Workshops. When booking with Eventbrite individuals will be required to provide their name and contact details. Eventbrite’s privacy policy can be found at the Privacy link located at the bottom of this page.

The City of Darebin also shares the data you provide for Bike Skills Workshops with Bikes@Work  - the professionals that deliver these workshops.  By registering and providing this information, you hereby agree to your data being shared with Bikes@Work so that they may have access to your emergency contact details, and that any feedback you provide may be used to improve the workshops they deliver.

item.title: Basic Bike Maintenance Workshop - Saturday 25 May 2019 (3pm - 5pm)
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
This workshop covers all the basics of how to maintain a bicycle. The instructor will use their bike to teach you how to remove wheels, complete a safety check, oil the chain, repair punctures and replace a tube. Bring along your own bike for a brief safety check and fitting. The workshop is an interactive session and invites questions and discussion.

Two hour parking is available in surrounding local streets (e.g., Milton Parade, Parslow Street: 4 min walk to venue); however, it is recommended that you catch a train to Tooronga Station and walk 1 minute to venue.

***No parking is available directly at the venue (aside from Tooronga Train station that may be hit or miss).

item.title: United Energy Around the Bay 2019
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
Join Melbourne's biggest bike riding celebration on Sunday 6 October - it's the best day you'll have on the bike all year!
United Energy Around the Bay is the best day you'll have on the bike all year! With nine ride options between 20km and the full 300km loop, there's a route for everyone to enjoy. Best of all, kids under 15 ride free for the 20km and 50km ride options! Everyone's invited back to the Albert Park event village to celebrate with food trucks, live music, kids activities and much more! We've got your back every step of the way with training rides, training plans and full on-route support to help you achieve your riding goals. Early bird entries receive a free event jersey (valued at $90, excludes free kids ticket)

item.title: Maintenance Class - Fitzroy North
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
As a Club 99 member, you're invited to come along to our store and attend a free basic maintenance class. Here's what we’ll cover:

1) Assessing your bike is safe to ride

GOAL: to gain confidence independently resolving simple mechanical issues
KEY LEARNINGS:

  • How to use quick releases.
  • How to use a mini tool / allen key set.
  • Basic competency with bolt tensions.
  • Basic competency with a pedal spanner.
  • Where to use grease.
  • Knowing when to get help.

2) Cleaning your bike

GOAL: to understand a process to follow to clean your bike
KEY LEARNINGS:

  • What to use to clean your bike.
  • Where to clean versus where to degrease.
  • How to apply and remove chain lube.
  • Which lubes for which conditions?


3) Changing a tyre and tube

GOAL: to be able to change your tube if you get a flat while out riding
KEY LEARNINGS:

  • What I need to change a tube?
  • What size tube I need for my bike?
  • Differences in valve types?
  • How to find and resolve what caused the flat?

What you need: 1 x pair of hands, and rolled up sleeves.

Note: Please do not bring your bike along to this class. We have limited space to allow you to work on your own bike, however you will be able to get hands-on with some tasks as we go.
